==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Eaglestone
<hw>Ea"gle*stone</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>A concretionary nodule of clay ironstone, of the size of a walnut
or larger, so called by the ancients, who believed that the eagle
transported these stones to her nest to facilitate the laying of her
eggs; a⟦eum⟧tites.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eaglet</ent>⟦br⟧
